WEBVTT

00:09.309 --> 00:10.542
It's our anniversary.

00:10.544 --> 00:11.443
You asked me
what I wanted,

00:11.445 --> 00:13.078
and I said just to
wake up with you.

00:13.080 --> 00:13.979
It's not gonna
happen, is it?

00:13.981 --> 00:16.248
(Elizabeth)
It's gonna happen.

00:17.617 --> 00:18.484
He asked me out on a date.

00:18.486 --> 00:21.120
I was hoping that
we could do something.

00:21.122 --> 00:21.653
Oh.

00:21.655 --> 00:22.688
The only thing
I really want

00:22.690 --> 00:24.857
is to be at home
with my real mom.

00:24.859 --> 00:26.025
That's all I want, too.

00:26.027 --> 00:27.226
So, you are into me.

00:27.228 --> 00:27.893
Max, what's wrong?

00:27.895 --> 00:29.561
You had me scared
out of my mind.

00:29.563 --> 00:31.697
Carter?

00:32.532 --> 00:35.167
Meet me here
tomorrow night.

00:35.169 --> 00:36.735
Tomorrow?

00:56.723 --> 00:59.224
(knocking)

01:05.331 --> 01:07.800
Happy birthday.

01:08.902 --> 01:11.837
My birthday?

01:11.839 --> 01:13.872
Today's my birthday?

01:13.874 --> 01:14.740
It's 6:06 a.m.

01:14.742 --> 01:18.644
You are exactly
17 years old.

01:21.014 --> 01:22.214
What happens now you--

01:22.216 --> 01:24.616
We wait 25 minutes,
then we wake up Taylor.

01:24.618 --> 01:26.885
But until then
she gets to sleep?

01:26.887 --> 01:28.654
'Fraid so.

01:28.656 --> 01:30.456
Even then,
she was smarter than me.

01:30.458 --> 01:32.157
(chuckles)

01:33.226 --> 01:35.727
Do we really have
to do this right now?

01:35.729 --> 01:36.862
It's so early.

01:36.864 --> 01:38.664
I will still be 17
in three hours.

01:38.666 --> 01:43.302
Come on, girls,
let's do this.

01:43.436 --> 01:46.972
(all)
Surprise! Happy birthday!

01:46.974 --> 01:48.607
Happy birthday!

01:48.609 --> 01:50.175
Okay.
So, what would you like?

01:50.177 --> 01:53.812
I've got bagels, I've got fruit,
and I am taking orders for eggs.

01:53.814 --> 01:55.848
Scrambled with
cream cheese, please.

01:55.850 --> 01:57.149
You don't get
to pick first.

01:57.151 --> 01:57.916
It's not your birthday.

01:57.918 --> 02:01.553
Maybe they'd like to open
some presents first.

02:06.092 --> 02:09.228
Um, let us discuss.

02:11.965 --> 02:13.165
Do you get this every year?

02:13.167 --> 02:15.667
No. This is usually
the worst day of the year.

02:15.669 --> 02:17.703
It's the annual reminder
you weren't here.

02:17.705 --> 02:19.805
I've always
dreaded my birthday.

02:19.807 --> 02:21.373
Okay, well,
I can top that.

02:21.375 --> 02:24.409
I didn't even know today
was my birthday.

02:26.846 --> 02:28.847
â™ª There you go

02:28.849 --> 02:31.917
â™ª There you stay

02:31.919 --> 02:33.619
â™ª Keeping low

02:33.621 --> 02:35.754
â™ª Never wanna play

02:35.756 --> 02:38.423
â™ª You've been up
and down, down â™ª

02:38.425 --> 02:40.425
â™ª You've been low, low, low

02:40.427 --> 02:45.531
â™ª Pretending to not
feel alone â™ª

02:45.533 --> 02:50.636
â™ª Pretending
to not feel alone â™ª

02:51.337 --> 02:54.940
So, you've been
celebrating your birthday

02:54.942 --> 02:56.675
on a different day?

02:56.677 --> 03:00.312
Yeah, I just turned 16
like six months ago.

03:00.314 --> 03:01.847
Weird.

03:01.849 --> 03:02.481
What day?

03:02.483 --> 03:06.118
It's no fun in there
without you.

03:07.453 --> 03:08.153
Here they are.

03:08.155 --> 03:09.454
You know what?
The last time you two

03:09.456 --> 03:13.325
celebrated a birthday together
you were three years old.

03:13.327 --> 03:14.259
Oh.

03:14.261 --> 03:15.561
Oh, yeah.

03:15.563 --> 03:19.831
Yeah, and you carried me
around on your shoulders.

03:21.301 --> 03:23.502
You remember that?

03:23.504 --> 03:24.703
Yeah.

03:24.705 --> 03:26.638
Yeah, you said it was

03:26.640 --> 03:28.340
so I could be as high
as a balloon.

03:28.342 --> 03:29.975
Oh, sweetheart,

03:29.977 --> 03:33.912
you make me feel
very special.

03:33.914 --> 03:34.947
Oh.

03:34.949 --> 03:36.949
Well, you were--
Uh, you are.

03:36.951 --> 03:39.184
Buddy, you have to
come over more often.

03:39.186 --> 03:40.986
Yeah, I don't even
remember that.

03:40.988 --> 03:41.820
What about me?

03:41.822 --> 03:43.455
I mean, do you remember
anything about Gammy?

03:43.457 --> 03:46.425
Was I wearing
a plaid dress?

03:46.427 --> 03:47.893
You were.

03:47.895 --> 03:49.194
I-I have a picture of it.

03:49.196 --> 03:50.862
Uh, it's in my wallet.
Where's my wallet?

03:50.864 --> 03:52.664
No, let's--
let's wait on that.

03:52.666 --> 03:53.498
Let's enjoy this moment.

03:53.500 --> 03:56.168
Do you remember the day
they were born?

03:56.170 --> 03:57.703
It was the best day
of my life.

03:57.705 --> 03:59.471
Okay if I eat this
in my room?

03:59.473 --> 04:01.640
I can still see you
holding one in each arm.

04:01.642 --> 04:03.675
"Do as you please, Grant."

04:03.677 --> 04:05.444
You know, after 14 years,

04:05.446 --> 04:08.714
you girls deserve
a birthday party.

04:08.716 --> 04:09.615
(Grandpa)
Sure.

04:09.617 --> 04:10.782
Um, I would love a party.

04:10.784 --> 04:14.253
Yeah, I'll, um--
I'll text my friend Bird.

04:14.255 --> 04:15.954
She'll send out
the bat signal.

04:15.956 --> 04:18.957
Yeah, let's talk about what
you're gonna wear tonight.

04:18.959 --> 04:19.391
Okay.

04:19.393 --> 04:22.294
Well, let's talk about
the most perfect gift,

04:22.296 --> 04:26.064
for the most perfect
birthday presents.

04:26.899 --> 04:28.166
Oh, a Macy's gift card.

04:28.168 --> 04:28.667
Thanks.

04:28.669 --> 04:31.903
Now you can go get yourself
something fabulous for tonight.

04:31.905 --> 04:32.604
Thank you.

04:32.606 --> 04:35.674
That means new,
something without holes in it.

04:35.676 --> 04:36.208
Right.

04:36.210 --> 04:38.910
And, you, slinky, sexy--
it wouldn't kill you.

04:38.912 --> 04:40.812
And some shoes, too.

04:40.814 --> 04:41.647
There's plenty on there.

04:41.649 --> 04:44.349
So, now, let's--
let's eat.
Okay.

04:46.853 --> 04:48.153
Can I talk to you a second?

04:48.155 --> 04:50.589
Sure.

04:51.190 --> 04:52.858
What did I do?

04:52.860 --> 04:53.558
I don't know.

04:53.560 --> 04:54.426
I'm trying to
figure that out.

04:54.428 --> 04:58.964
Your husband has been asking me
all kinds of questions

04:58.966 --> 05:00.899
about some spa package

05:00.901 --> 05:03.268
that I got at
a silent auction that--

05:03.270 --> 05:05.170
Oh, my God,
what did you say?

05:05.172 --> 05:06.271
No, it's fine.

05:06.273 --> 05:07.372
I rolled with it.

05:07.374 --> 05:09.508
You "rolled with it"?

05:09.510 --> 05:11.276
Are you cheating
on David?

05:11.278 --> 05:13.378
Is there somebody else?

05:13.380 --> 05:15.881
Mom, it's very complicated.

05:15.883 --> 05:19.251
Please tell me you're
seeing someone else.

05:19.253 --> 05:20.218
What?

05:20.220 --> 05:23.255
Nothing would make me
happier than if you finally

05:23.257 --> 05:24.823
unloaded this loser.

05:24.825 --> 05:26.591
If you need me
to cover for you,

05:26.593 --> 05:27.659
I'll do it happily.

05:27.661 --> 05:29.361
Just, please,
no more silent auctions.

05:29.363 --> 05:32.564
I cannot have people thinking
I go to silent auctions.

05:32.566 --> 05:34.032
I...

05:34.034 --> 05:36.001
What else is
a mother for?

05:36.003 --> 05:38.570
I'm pretty sure not that.

05:38.572 --> 05:43.475
Okay, I have to get ready
for that birthday party.

05:43.477 --> 05:45.844
Oh, you think you're
doing that birthday party

05:45.846 --> 05:46.812
in those drabby drabs?

05:46.814 --> 05:48.180
No. In fact,
you know what?

05:48.182 --> 05:49.147
I'm getting my credit card,

05:49.149 --> 05:50.182
and you're going shopping
with the girls.

05:50.184 --> 05:53.085
We can pay for
our own clothes, Joan.

05:53.087 --> 05:54.353
Can you?

05:58.057 --> 05:59.858
Hey, hey,
you want a donut?

05:59.860 --> 06:00.859
Mm-hmm, mm-hmm.

06:00.861 --> 06:03.528
Thank you.
They're really good.

06:03.530 --> 06:04.696
Love a good donut.

06:04.698 --> 06:07.899
Mm, so good.

06:07.901 --> 06:10.235
Carter, you want one?

06:24.517 --> 06:26.151
Mom?

06:26.153 --> 06:29.755
Mom, where are you?

06:33.192 --> 06:34.893
Oh, my...

06:34.895 --> 06:37.929
I can't believe
you did this.

06:37.931 --> 06:38.630
Of course.

06:38.632 --> 06:41.500
It's my absolute
favorite day of the year,

06:41.502 --> 06:43.402
the day you made me a mother.

06:43.404 --> 06:47.139
(both laughing)

06:49.342 --> 06:50.675
And we feel so lucky

06:50.677 --> 06:53.812
to have our whole family
under one roof.

06:53.814 --> 06:55.113
Mom's making a toast?

06:55.115 --> 06:55.847
So glad.

06:55.849 --> 06:56.515
There's champagne in it.

06:56.517 --> 07:01.453
Okay, anyway, I just wanted
to say thank you

07:01.455 --> 07:06.858
for making me
a mother and Elizabeth.

07:06.860 --> 07:08.794
For God sake's,
enough already.

07:08.796 --> 07:09.628
She's your mom.

07:09.630 --> 07:11.096
Call her mom.
Mom.

07:11.098 --> 07:11.830
Don't use that tone.

07:11.832 --> 07:13.064
Cheers.
Anyway, let's toast.

07:13.066 --> 07:15.967
(all)
Cheers.

07:15.969 --> 07:18.203
Happy birthday.

07:18.205 --> 07:19.805
Cheers.
Excuse me.

07:19.807 --> 07:21.206
Happy birthday.

07:26.479 --> 07:28.413
(knocking)

07:28.415 --> 07:30.749
Um, just a sec.

07:37.123 --> 07:43.395
You with a hidden suitcase,
that's never a good sign.

07:49.969 --> 07:51.369
(sighs)

07:53.639 --> 07:56.908
I saw my mom.

07:56.910 --> 08:00.712
Around here she's known
as "the kidnapper".

08:05.651 --> 08:08.820
Does this mean
you're leaving?

08:11.390 --> 08:14.292
Going back to her?

08:14.294 --> 08:15.660
Tay...

08:15.662 --> 08:17.662
When?

08:18.865 --> 08:19.931
It better not be today.

08:19.933 --> 08:21.867
I told you I didn't
know about today.

08:21.869 --> 08:22.400
But now you do,

08:22.402 --> 08:26.538
so can you reschedule
devastating your family?

08:26.540 --> 08:28.907
It's not up to me.

08:28.909 --> 08:30.108
Yes, it is.

08:30.110 --> 08:31.643
It's totally up to you.

08:31.645 --> 08:33.745
It's clearly not
up to me or Grant.

08:33.747 --> 08:36.248
Is there anyone whose opinion
matters to you?

08:36.250 --> 08:37.849
You don't think
this is hard for me, too?

08:37.851 --> 08:41.653
It's really hard,
Taylor, okay?

08:41.655 --> 08:42.454
But I can't stay here

08:42.456 --> 08:45.090
and be with my mom
at the same time, okay?

08:45.092 --> 08:46.291
I have to choose.

08:46.293 --> 08:47.125
So, you could do that?

08:47.127 --> 08:49.027
You could spend
today with us,

08:49.029 --> 08:50.529
have us throw you a party,

08:50.531 --> 08:51.429
pose for pictures,

08:51.431 --> 08:54.165
and then let us
wake up tomorrow morning

08:54.167 --> 08:55.500
and relive that nightmare.

08:55.502 --> 08:56.501
I'm sorry.

08:56.503 --> 08:58.703
I don't give a crap
if you're sorry.

08:58.705 --> 09:02.374
Answer the question,
could you do that?

09:02.376 --> 09:03.041
Because if you can,

09:03.043 --> 09:06.378
then-- then you must
really hate us.

09:10.049 --> 09:11.983
(sighs)

09:12.485 --> 09:15.253
Clearly there's
nothing I can say.

09:15.255 --> 09:17.455
Yes, there is.

09:17.457 --> 09:20.458
"I'm staying."

09:22.228 --> 09:24.729
(scoffs)

09:24.731 --> 09:30.735
Everyone always says
it's so great being a twin.

09:30.737 --> 09:31.736
They wouldn't say that

09:31.738 --> 09:34.673
if they had to be
your twin.

09:42.949 --> 09:44.516
(sighs)

09:54.594 --> 09:57.562
Tay, come on.

09:57.564 --> 09:59.931
All right, fine.

09:59.933 --> 10:03.101
But you're missing out
on some really cute dresses.

10:04.537 --> 10:07.639
I think Max would
really like this one.

10:13.346 --> 10:15.146
How are things
with you and Max?

10:15.148 --> 10:16.615
What difference
does it make

10:16.617 --> 10:18.383
since you won't
be here tomorrow?

10:18.385 --> 10:20.185
You guys finding anything
you like?

10:20.187 --> 10:23.054
Um, yeah, tons of stuff.
Yeah, yeah.

10:25.191 --> 10:27.025
Who else knows?

10:28.027 --> 10:31.062
Max.

10:31.064 --> 10:32.664
He met Lori at
the Quick-and-Easy

10:32.666 --> 10:33.531
where he works,

10:33.533 --> 10:37.402
which he was not
happy about.

10:37.404 --> 10:38.770
And this was yesterday?

10:38.772 --> 10:40.005
Mm-hmm.

10:40.007 --> 10:41.873
And he was
texting you?

10:41.875 --> 10:43.508
Yeah, like a hundred times.

10:43.510 --> 10:46.444
Oh, and Crash
was with me,

10:46.446 --> 10:47.245
so he met her as well.

10:47.247 --> 10:49.581
Well, at least
she didn't kidnap you.

10:49.583 --> 10:52.283
I guess that's
an improvement.

10:54.420 --> 10:56.321
Taylor, I don't want you
to hate me.

10:56.323 --> 10:58.690
Stay and I won't hate you.

10:58.692 --> 11:01.726
I can't stay.

11:01.728 --> 11:03.395
And I could walk
right over there

11:03.397 --> 11:05.964
and tell Mom,
and then you'd have to.

11:07.633 --> 11:08.900
What about Grant?

11:08.902 --> 11:10.468
I can't think about Grant.

11:10.470 --> 11:13.271
You guys ready
to try on some stuff?

11:14.240 --> 11:15.774
Should we even bother?

11:17.209 --> 11:18.510
Well, we're here.

11:18.512 --> 11:20.812
Fine.

11:26.819 --> 11:28.620
Guys, let me see.

11:28.622 --> 11:29.754
(Carter)
I'm not ready yet.

11:29.756 --> 11:30.555
(Taylor)
Yeah, me neither.

11:30.557 --> 11:33.224
We cannot leave this store
empty-handed.

11:33.226 --> 11:35.727
I found something
I like.

11:35.729 --> 11:37.829
Good, let's see.

11:40.633 --> 11:43.435
Taylor,
you look beautiful.

11:43.437 --> 11:44.469
I really like it.

11:44.471 --> 11:46.371
You have to wear this
to the party.

11:46.373 --> 11:47.939
Oh, I think I found
my dress!

11:47.941 --> 11:49.874
Great, come out.

11:55.047 --> 11:56.781
(chuckles)

11:57.516 --> 11:58.917
Okay, no contest.

11:58.919 --> 12:00.452
You win.

12:01.253 --> 12:04.989
You both look spectacular.

12:08.327 --> 12:10.261
I want you to have it.

12:10.263 --> 12:12.263
Tay, no, come on.

12:12.265 --> 12:14.499
Yes, it's your last--

12:14.501 --> 12:17.502
Your last what?

12:20.573 --> 12:22.907
It's your last time
I'm ever gonna be

12:22.909 --> 12:24.509
this generous to you.

12:25.511 --> 12:27.812
Okay, you're both
getting the dresses.

12:27.814 --> 12:30.115
No.
Oh, no, come on.

12:30.117 --> 12:31.149
That would be pretty
humiliating.

12:31.151 --> 12:33.284
Way too humiliating.
Come here.

12:33.286 --> 12:34.819
Come here.

12:37.723 --> 12:39.023
What?

12:40.426 --> 12:40.759
Oh.

12:40.761 --> 12:42.961
Last time you had
a birthday party...

12:42.963 --> 12:48.833
...together, you both wore
the same dress.

12:52.905 --> 12:58.877
Tay, be my twin again?

12:58.879 --> 13:00.178
Please?

13:02.982 --> 13:05.250
Okay.

13:05.252 --> 13:07.018
I'm gonna go get dressed.

13:10.089 --> 13:12.056
Can I hold on
to this for a sec?

13:12.058 --> 13:14.659
Yeah, yeah.
I just wanna look at it.

13:14.661 --> 13:17.061
Thanks.

13:31.477 --> 13:33.812
Hey.
Hey.

13:33.814 --> 13:34.612
Chinese for dinner?

13:34.614 --> 13:37.582
Uh, the place with
good scallion pancakes?

13:37.584 --> 13:40.018
Oh, you got it.

13:40.020 --> 13:40.952
Oh, um--

13:40.954 --> 13:43.955
I need a baby picture of me
for school.

13:43.957 --> 13:46.291
They're doing some
section in the yearbook.

13:46.293 --> 13:47.392
Do you have one?

13:47.394 --> 13:48.827
A baby picture?

13:48.829 --> 13:53.631
Oh, honey, don't you remember
when this building flooded

13:53.633 --> 13:55.633
a few years back?

13:55.635 --> 13:56.668
No.

13:56.670 --> 13:59.337
Well, I had all the pictures
in boxes in the basement.

13:59.339 --> 14:00.772
They all got destroyed.

14:00.774 --> 14:02.774
All of them did?

14:03.642 --> 14:04.943
Okay.

14:04.945 --> 14:08.980
I do have one picture,
but it's my only one,

14:08.982 --> 14:11.783
so I would absolutely
have to get it back.

14:11.785 --> 14:13.952
Okay.
Mm-hmm.

14:16.722 --> 14:17.956
Oh.

14:18.824 --> 14:21.759
How have I never
seen this before?

14:21.761 --> 14:23.228
Why is it laminated?

14:23.230 --> 14:26.297
I wanted to protect it,
you know?

14:28.567 --> 14:31.202
(Elizabeth)
Carter?

14:32.638 --> 14:35.773
Uh, just a sec.

14:36.842 --> 14:42.580
I can't remember the last time
I was this happy.

14:42.582 --> 14:44.115
You're a great mom.

14:44.117 --> 14:48.519
It's really nice
to see you happy.

14:57.563 --> 15:01.766
I was just telling her
what a great mom she is.

15:04.603 --> 15:07.338
I don't know
what's gotten into her.

15:09.141 --> 15:10.441
Thanks for showing me this.

15:10.443 --> 15:12.243
Oh, yeah.
Hey, um,

15:12.245 --> 15:15.179
do have any other
baby pictures of me?

15:15.181 --> 15:17.649
Oh, Lord, boxes.
Anytime you wanna see them.

15:17.651 --> 15:22.487
As soon as we get home?

15:22.489 --> 15:23.955
Yeah.

15:23.957 --> 15:27.325
â™ª

15:31.030 --> 15:32.463
(knocking)

15:32.465 --> 15:33.898
Who is it?

15:34.867 --> 15:36.534
Max.

15:36.536 --> 15:37.402
Hey.

15:37.404 --> 15:39.103
Look at these.

15:39.105 --> 15:40.872
Look how cute I was?

15:40.874 --> 15:41.839
Oh.

15:41.841 --> 15:44.509
Oh, yeah.

15:44.511 --> 15:46.244
That's the cutest one.

15:46.879 --> 15:47.512
That's Taylor.

15:47.514 --> 15:51.416
Hey, can we talk about
what happened last night?

15:53.118 --> 15:54.485
Yeah.

15:58.023 --> 15:59.757
What did you decide?

15:59.759 --> 16:02.093
Obviously, I'm going.

16:02.095 --> 16:05.263
Okay, then, this is a very
important conversation,

16:05.265 --> 16:11.035
because I strongly
feel you should not go.

16:11.037 --> 16:11.769
You know what, Max?

16:11.771 --> 16:13.071
That's not
really your decision.

16:13.073 --> 16:14.572
Yeah, I know,
this is up to you.

16:14.574 --> 16:16.808
But I know things that
you don't know,

16:16.810 --> 16:19.944
which I believe would
influence your decision.

16:19.946 --> 16:20.878
Okay, well,
you know what?

16:20.880 --> 16:22.246
You're not gonna change
my decision.

16:22.248 --> 16:24.015
So, if it's something
I wouldn't wanna know,

16:24.017 --> 16:25.616
